Catching an Exception: Basic Syntax

Basic Syntax of the try-catch statement...

Option 1: Try-Catch Block

try {
    statements-that-might-throw-exception;
} catch (Exception e) {
    e.printStackTrace();
}

Option 2: "throws" Keyword

public void doit(int x) throw Exception {
    statements-that-might-throw-an-exception;
}

Exception Class -- Must be Imported!

Two useful Methods:
1. e.printStackTrace(); //Prints the call stack
2. e.getMessage();  //Prints the associated Message

